01/06/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The single Intelligence and Security Agency (OSA) in BiH began operating Tuesday (1 June), the Office of the High Representative announced. Its establishment is in line with reforms in the security sector and the abolition of separate services in the two entities. The newly-appointed head and deputy head of OSA, Almir Dzuvo and Risto Zaric, assumed their duties at a formal ceremony Tuesday. Their first task is to appoint interim co-ordinators in Sarajevo and Banja Luka. The establishment of OSA was initially planned for 1 January but was delayed by administrative issues. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 01/06/04)
